original: Ekberg, Alf Skoglar, arkitekt, Skövde, f. 24/5/93 i Skövde av CTI-img. o. kassören Isidor E. o. Anne-Sofie Strömbom. G. 1. 25 m. Inez Paulsen; 2. m. Märta Östergren. Barn: Anne-Charlotte f. 26, Bengt 27. — Genomg. Borås tekn. gymn. Anst. v. Gbgs stadsing :kont. 15 o. 18, h. arkit. Ernst Torulf i Gbg 16-17 o. 22-23, h. bygg-n:råd. Georg A. Nilsson i Sthlm 19-22 o. 23-30, eg. verks. fr. 30. Medl. av Tekn:fören. i Skövde o. Borås o. Tekn. lärov. ing :fören. Hobbiies : akva-r e#målin., oilj emåil n.
translated: Ekberg, Alf Skoglar, architect, born on May 24, 1893 in Skövde to CTI-img. and cashier Isidor E. and Anne-Sofie Strömbom. He was married twice, first to Inez Paulsen in 1925 and then to Märta Östergren. They have two children, Anne-Charlotte born in 1926 and Bengt born in 1927. He attended Borås technical high school and apprenticed with architect Ernst Torulf in Gothenburg in 1916-1917 and 1922-1923 and with building councilor Georg A. Nilsson in Stockholm in 1919-1922 and 1923-1930, later running his own firm from 1930. He was a member of the Technical Society in Skövde and Borås, and of the Technical School of Engineering. His hobbies include watercolor painting and oil painting.
